@jwhonce thanks for reply.
the solution may work, but not general, it's difficult to ask every my user to do that.

i try to import this project in my golang project and build a proxied `bindings.Connection`, but the `clientKey` is unexported， i can't add my proxied Connection object into a ctx with `clientKey`.

is this a feature should be support ? i’d like to make a pr to support this feature.

1. add a proxy arg in `NewConnection(ctx context.Context, uri string) (context.Context, error)`;

2. or export `bindings.clientKey`,  then user can put a customed `bindings.Connection` into `context.Context`;

I prefer the second one, which will not affect others when they update their podman bindings library, but give a way for people who want to custom their Connection.

@jwhonce great idea! 

about the example  detail,  `bindings.NewConnection(...)` always return a nil `conn`,  cause `pingNewConnection`  will fail without a custom `http.client`. 

how about  this one `bindings.NewConnectionWithClient(ctx context.Context, uri string, client *http.Client)(context.Context, error)`
